id=1116 SUPERINTENDENT\u2019S UPDATE \u2013 FEBRUARY 26].  Accessed April 8, 2009. {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n\n==July 2008 fire==\nOn July 11\u201312, 2008, a fire destroyed one of the school's main buildings, which held the science lab, classrooms, the home economics area, and the library.<ref name=USA>\"Across the USA: Oregon: Glide\", [[USA Today]], July 14, 2008, P. 8a.</ref><ref name=KPIC>\"Investigators still trying to determine cause of Glide High School Fire,\" [[KPIC]] News, July 14, 2008, found at [http://www.kpic.com/news/25455249.html KPIC News] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713170801/http://www.kpic.com/news/25455249.html |date=2011-07-13 }}.  Accessed July 15, 2008.</ref><ref name=NR>Vicki Menard, \"Fire engulfs Glide High School main building: Student information saved,\" ''[[The News-Review]]'', found at [http://www.nrtoday.com/article/20080712/NEWS/410678928/0/FRONTPAGE News-Review story].  Accessed July 15, 2008.</ref><ref name=AP>AP, \"Fire at Southern Oregon high school,\" July 12, 2008, found at [http://www.oregonlive.com/newsflash/index.ssf?/base/news-25/121592281253560.xml&storylist=orlocal AP Story at Oregon Live website] of ''[[The Oregonian]]''. Accessed July 15, 2008.</ref>  Many classrooms, offices, the gymnasium, and a weight room were saved by firefighters from the Glide Volunteer Fire department and other nearby companies.<ref name=KPIC/> The school district was already replacing or rehabilitating some of the areas to have classrooms ready for the fall 2008 term, which began in September.<ref name=KPIC/> The fire was believed to be caused by a plumber's torch in a classroom of the main building.<ref name=USA/><ref name=KPIC/>\n\n==Academics==\nIn 2019, 93% of the school's seniors received a [[high school diploma]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/education/index.ssf/2009/06/high_school_dropout_rates.html|title=State releases high school graduation rates|date=2009-06-30|work=[[T