o]], [[California]]\n| ESPN\n| 7:30 PM\n| #23 [[2015 Wisconsin Badgers football team|Wisconsin]]\n| 23\n| '''USC'''\n| '''21'''\n|-style=\"background:#CCFFCC;\"\n| [[2016 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]]\n| Friday, January 1, 2016\n| [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]]\n| [[Pasadena, California]]\n| ESPN\n| 2:10 PM\n| '''#5 Stanford''' \n| '''45'''\n| #6 [[2015 Iowa Hawkeyes football team|Iowa]]\n| 16\n|-style=\"background:#FFCCCC;\"\n| [[2016 Alamo Bowl (January)|Alamo Bowl]]\n| Saturday, January 2, 2016\n| [[Alamodome]]\n| [[San Antonio, Texas]]\n| ESPN\n| 3:45 PM\n| #11 [[2015 TCU Horned Frogs football team|TCU]]\n| 47\n| '''#15 Oregon'''\n| 41<sup>3OT</sup>\n|-style=\"background:#FFCCCC;\"\n| [[2016 Cactus Bowl (January)|Cactus Bowl]]\n| Saturday, January 2, 2016\n| [[Chase Field]]\n| [[Phoenix, Arizona]]\n| ESPN\n| 8:15 PM\n| '''[[2015 West Virginia Mountaineers football team|West Virginia]]'''\n| '''43'''\n| Arizona State\n| 42\n|}\n\n==Pac-12 vs Power Conference matchups==\n\nThis is a list of the [[power conference]] teams ([[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]], [[Big Ten Conference|Big 10]], [[Big 12 Conference|Big 12]] and [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]]) the Pac-12 plays in the non-conference (''Rankings from the AP Poll''):\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date !! Visitor !! Home !! Site !! Significance !! Score\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n| September 3 || [[2015 Michigan Wolverines football team|Michigan]] || '''Utah''' || [[Rice-Eccles Stadium]] \u2022 [[Salt Lake City, Utah]] ||  || UTAH '''W''' 24\u201317\n|- bgcolor=ffccc\n| September 5 || '''Arizona State''' || [[2015 Texas A&M Aggies football team|Texas A&M]] || [[NRG Stadium]] \u2022 [[Houston, TX]] || [[Texas Kickoff]] || TAMU '''L''' 17\u201338\n|- bgcolor=ffccc\n| September 5 || '''Stanford''' || [[2015 Northwestern Wildcats football team|Northwestern]] || [[Ryan Field (stadium)|Ryan Field]] \u2022 [[Evanston, IL]] || || NW '''L''' 6\u201316\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n| September 5 || [[2015 Virginia Cavaliers football team|Vi